{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01U3eozAEJoWX5urnNsbg5qe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see an issue - the strategic merge patch preserved the OLD volumeMounts (config, file-realm) as well as the new mounts I specified. The strategic merge for containers uses the \"name\" as the merge key. When I specified the main container with volumeMounts, it MERGED the volumeMounts rather than replacing them.\n\nThe result has:\n- Old config subPath mount (elasticsearch.yml)\n- Old file-realm subPath mounts (users, users_roles, roles.yml)\n- New es-config-vol mount (/es-config)\n- New es-secure-settings mount\n- Certs mount\n\nActually, having both the ES_PATH_CONF=/es-config environment variable and the old subPath mounts might work fine since ES will read from /es-config and ignore the old mounts at /usr/share/elasticsearch/config. But I need to verify that ES_PATH_CONF actually points to where all the required config files are located.\n\nThe init container copies elasticsearch.yml and the security files (users, users_roles, roles.yml) to /es-config, and ES reads everything from there. The old subPath mounts just sit unused. However, the certs are mounted at /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs, and elasticsearch.yml references them with absolute paths like /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt. Since ES reads elasticsearch.yml from /es-config, those absolute paths in the config file might not resolve correctly if the certs aren't actually at that location.\n\nWait, the certs volume IS mounted at /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs, so the absolute paths should work fine. The setup is sound: the init container prepares /es-config with all the config files, ES_PATH_CONF points to /es-config, and the certs remain accessible at their original absolute path.\n\nNow I need to verify the file-realm volume is properly defined in the StatefulSet volumes list—checking if it was already there in the original spec since the main container references it in its volumeMounts. The original StatefulSet's last-applied-configuration doesn't show the file-realm volumes, but they're present in the current spec after 7 generations of updates, meaning they were added by a previous patch before my changes. My patch then added the secure-settings and config volumes along with the init containers for permissions and keystore setup.\n\nNow I'm waiting to see the rolling restart of the first elasticsearch pod and whether the init containers execute properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":486,"cache_read_input_tokens":91059,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":486},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49dceff0-8760-4181-b837-19ed3a1bcd66","uuid":"3beabba2-206a-4bfc-aa6a-bd9de02ffe4c","request_id":"req_011CcfuLTJjHCFax9A2s18JH"}
