{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HiSWaryes2ELLgSNNCSP12","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** MinIO had no Kubernetes Service (DNS unreachable), `es-secure-settings` Secret didn't exist, and no S3 credentials were configured in Elasticsearch.\n\n**What was fixed:**\n\n1. **Created MinIO Service** (`minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`) so MinIO is reachable from within the cluster.\n\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` Secret** containing `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` with MinIO credentials — credentials are never in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars.\n\n3. **Updated `es-config` ConfigMap** to add `s3.client.default.endpoint` and `s3.client.default.protocol: http` (non-sensitive settings only).\n\n4. **Updated the StatefulSet** with a `setup-keystore` init container that:\n   - Reads credentials from the mounted `es-secure-settings` Secret\n   - Populates a fresh Elasticsearch keystore using `elasticsearch-keystore` with those credentials\n   - Copies all config files into a shared `es-config-vol` emptyDir, so the main container picks up the keystore at the standard path (`/usr/share/elasticsearch/config`)\n   - Runs on every pod restart, keeping credentials durable via the Secret\n\n5. **Created `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO.\n\n6. **Registered `minio-repo`** snapshot repository and created **`snapshot-1`** — which completed successfully (`SUCCESS`, 2/2 shards)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":991,"cache_read_input_tokens":111837,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":991},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49dceff0-87